quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  15,1,"Alif Lām Ra. Those are the signs{1}of the Scripture and an evident Recital{2}.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used isayat(singularayah). Ayahmeans ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an,like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose.Each such unit isconsidered a ‘sign’from God.|2:The Arabic word used is Qur’an which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  15,2,"Perhaps those who have denied will wish they had been Muslims."
  15,3,"Let<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>them eat and enjoy and be distracted by<i class=""s"">(false) </i>hope, for they willcome to know."
  15,4,"For in no way did We annihilate any town except that it had a known written decree."
  15,5,"No community can advance its time, nor can they delay it."
  15,6,"And they said, “O you upon whom the Reminder has been bestowed from on high, very truly you are insane."
  15,7,"If only you would bring us the angels, if you are one of the truthful!”"
  15,8,"<span class=""h"">We bestow<sup foot_note=""80346"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">not the angels</span>from on high except with the truth{2}, and in no way would they{3}then be respited.",footnotes:2:According to Ibn ʻAshour and other exegetes, ‘with the truth’ means ‘for a purpose’.|3:The deniers.
  15,9,"Indeed, We—We alone—have bestowed the Reminder from on high, and We will most surely preserve it."
  15,10,"And most surely We sent<i class=""s"">(messengers) </i>before you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>to the sects of the ancients,"
  15,11,"but no messenger comes{1}to them but they used to ridicule him.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an speaks about the prophets using present tense; this should be pondered by the reader.
  15,12,"Thus We insert it{1}into the hearts of the criminals—",footnotes:1:The Reminder.
  15,13,"they do not believe in it, though the rule of<i class=""s"">(God regarding) </i>the ancients has surely passed before."
  15,14,"And if We were to open for them a gateway into the sky so that they were to continue ascending through it,"
  15,15,"they would surely say, “Indeed, our sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i>have been <span class=""h"">stupefied<sup foot_note=""80351"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>; rather, we are a people bewitched.”"
